Minister of Higher Education and Training Blade Nzimande said he has acted against improprieties at universities. JOHANNESBURG - Higher Education Minister Blade Nzimande has refuted reports that he has failed to act on allegations of financial irregularities and sexual harassment at two universities in Limpopo. Times Live reported that Nzimande came under fire in Parliament for not taking decisive action on the allegations. READ: 2020 academic year remains on course: Nzimande Nzimande appeared before the Portfolio Committee on Higher Education, Science and Technology on Tuesday last week. The minister said he acted on the allegations of sexual harassment, financial irregularities and maladministration at the two universities.